description:

The 'Sailing Nervous' series will trace their progress as they attempt to make their dream a reality. From dreaming of sailing, to learning how to sail, to buying a boat, to fixing the boat up for sailing, and then finally beginning their journey aboard, they invite you to come along.

description:
This channel is more then just about sailing... It's about 2 young people that fell in love and worked hard to accomplish their dream.
After building their sailboat they sailed off into the sunset. 30 + years later they are still living their dream! Come sail with us! Explore exotic places and see how we made it possible. We've lived off the grid for the last 30 years for no more then poverty wages. We built  Emerald Steel  and have been living aboard and cruising most of the time since her completion in 1987. Suzie did all of the welding and Jules did all the cutting, grinding and fitting. We were 23 and 36 years old at the beginning of our project in 1985.  Our general daily electrical usage is provided by 2- 80 watt solar panels. We also have a 7 kw diesel generator which powers our 1000 gal. per day water maker - designed and built by Jules  (although we only use 10 gal per day), hydraulic windlass for our 1/2" chain ,mig welder and plasma cutter which we carry on board.
title: Sailing Emerald Steel

 She has a 13 HP Internal Yanmar Diesel and 5 Sails, 8' Beam and was in need of much work.  I have taken her out on a few trial runs, she is a Dream.

 I want to share all the Restoration Work I do with you, the other Dreamers who want boats of their own!  This is my 3rd Sailboat I have restored. I want to save you $$ and get your Dreams Going by my video's and examples and show what many don't or I could never find and had to create. 

This Sailboat in the end cost me 0 Dollars.  Through it being abandoned, the owner missing, I tracked it back though owners until I found one.  She signed the boat over to me for free!

Follow and Subscribe as I redo her Electrical, Plumbing, Wood Work and Rigging. 

This will prepare me for my next  Dream ... Get her all Ship Shape and Sail to the Bahamas !

description:
Sailrite is a second generation family business. Founded in 1969 the business was intended to serve a function no other business had ever served as a source of instruction and materials for amateur sailmakers. At that time the very concept of "amateur sailmaking" was new. Sailmaking was generally believed a black art. Sailrite has largely changed this view and today is well known as a provider of sail kits to serious racers, boat builders and sailors owning good old boats. These individuals build sails to broaden their self-reliance and power their boats. Sailmaking is a great deal of fun and a very satisfying hobby. 

Sailrite is a full-stock retailer of thousands of canvas supplies, tools, fabrics, kits, and videos including the Ultrafeed LSZ-1 sewing machine and complete Sunbrella fabric lines. Sailrite can help you learn more, spend less, and do-it-yourself.
title: Sailrite

description:
Welcome to my channel dedicated to sailing.

Back in 2006 the wife and I noticed our business was falling off. By late 2007 it was apparent that we were headed into a recession. We researched a LOT and came to the conclusion that things were starting to fail. We made a decision to buy a sailboat, learn to sail, pay off all debt and move aboard. Our idea was that from then on we should just invest what we had into tangibles for our retirement instead of giving our money to a bank/broker/investor that would end up stealing or losing it.

We're over half way to our goal. We live aboard 50% of the time. Our money does not go into an account to be lost or devalued by our government/banking system, but into our sailboat and food supplies that will last us months, if not years. We plan to sail south into the Pacific and island hop. We will farm the sea, fish, grow food here and there, barter services, and visit islands.

Come join us while we learn and ready ourselves for our voyage!
title: Tom SailBeforeSunset

After that I produced my first film in the Project BlueSphere series "California to Colombia". 

After that I lived in the San Blas Islands of Panama with the Kuna Indians for a year before transiting the Panama Canal and single handing my 28' sailboat "Namaste" 8000 miles across the Pacific to Brisbane Australia "What a ride"! 

If you would like more information please check out www.projectbluesphere.com. From my website you can read daily logs, check out pictures and video clips, or buy my DVD's. 

Cheers guys!

Alex Dorsey

White Spots are undiscovered areas on each individual's personal map of life. These are not necessarily places you want to go, but can be any kind of dream that you want to come true.

The purpose of WhiteSpotPirates (WSP) is to bring people one step closer to putting their own dreams into reality, to build up a community that inspires and supports each other. 

The weekly video documentation "Untie The Lines" is WSP's first project. It is about a young woman who bought an old sailing boat in Panama and wants to try and sail the word. Future plans of WSP are to feature different stories of a wide range of "Pirates".

Become a Patron (www.patreon.com/WhiteSpotPirates) of UNTIE THE LINES now or use PayPal (https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_s-xclick&hosted_button_id=GWBYVNU5LENLS) to support this project. Thank you so much!

description:
One blistery winter morning four years ago, Erik and Meagan stumbled onto a plan... two boats, several uninsured surgeries, countless unforgettable friendships, and a whole lot of work later they, along with their furry companion, Nikka, finally sailed out under the Golden Gate Bridge and turned left.  Traveling South along the west coast of the Americas, and then on to ...?  Your guess is as good as theirs, maybe they’ll sail over to Hawaii, maybe sail around the world.
 
They once heard a wise man say “routine is the time killer,” and they took it to heart.  They are sailing the Pacific Ocean attempting to live every day with their eyes open and minds engaged.  For the first time living each day excited about the possibility of tomorrow instead of dreading or trying to control it.
 
Follow them along on their journey and share in their joys and challenges and see where their crazy sailing adventure lands them.

description:
About
We LOVE sailing, We LOVE travelling, and we LOVE making videos about it. Delos is a 53 foot sailboat home to young adventurous souls sailing around the world! Welcome aboard!

Mission
It’s simple really- we just want to make you SMILE! We do this because we LOVE it. Given our short time on this AMAZING PLANET there’s absolutely, positively, nothing more we’d rather be doing with our time! We hope by sharing this adventure you will find some inspiration in your life.

Description
Delos is a 53 foot Amel Super Maramu. She was built in La Rochelle France in 2000 and has since seen what most sailboats dream of seeing. She has completed a circumnavigation and is now on her second voyage around the world. She is a sailing ketch (2 masts) and has enough room to comfortably sleep 6 people. Delos is able to turn salt water into fresh water, sun into energy, provide food and shelter, travel for months on end without visiting a dock and best of all, be the place we call home.
title: SV Delos Sailing
